docs.abstract: Senators Marco Rubio and Elizabeth Warren offered bipartisan legislation that would end a practice that critics say prevents those who defaulted on loans from paying what they owe.
docs.snippet: Senators Marco Rubio and Elizabeth Warren offered bipartisan legislation that would end a practice that critics say prevents those who defaulted on loans from paying what they owe.
docs.lead_paragraph: Senators Marco Rubio and Elizabeth Warren introduced a bill on Thursday that would prevent states from suspending residents’ driver’s and professional licenses over unpaid federal student loans. Critics have called the practice a self-defeating approach that denies borrowers the means to pay their debts.

headline.main: Rubio and Warren Seek to Protect Licenses of Student-Loan Debtors
headline.print_headline: Plan Would Protect Debtors With Unpaid Student Loans

docs.abstract: The ride-hailing company is appealing a ban in its largest European market. The case is a major test of changes made by its new chief executive, Dara Khosrowshahi.
docs.snippet: The ride-hailing company is appealing a ban in its largest European market. The case is a major test of changes made by its new chief executive, Dara Khosrowshahi.
docs.lead_paragraph: LONDON — Dara Khosrowshahi’s 10-month tenure as Uber’s chief executive has been marked by a prolonged public relations campaign to apologize for the company’s past misdeeds and portray the once proudly combative start-up as a reformed corporate citizen.

headline.main: Uber Claims to Have Changed. A London Judge Will Decide.

docs.abstract: A Senate committee voted in favor of the Music Modernization Act, moving it one step closer to becoming law. It aims to modernize the analog-era music copyright law.
docs.snippet: A Senate committee voted in favor of the Music Modernization Act, moving it one step closer to becoming law. It aims to modernize the analog-era music copyright law.
docs.lead_paragraph: For a decade, the music industry has promoted a motley series of copyright bills to Congress, only to watch them fail.

headline.main: New Way to Pay Songwriters and Musicians in the Streaming Age Advances
headline.print_headline: A Senate Committee Votes for Peace in the Music Industry

docs.abstract: European leaders agreed to a plan that would finally take Athens off financial life support, effectively declaring an end to a crisis that nearly wrecked the euro.
docs.snippet: European leaders agreed to a plan that would finally take Athens off financial life support, effectively declaring an end to a crisis that nearly wrecked the euro.
docs.lead_paragraph: BRUSSELS — European leaders announced early Friday a plan that would finally take Greece off financial life support, effectively declaring an end to a regional debt crisis that nearly destroyed the euro.

headline.main: Greece Prepares to Stagger Back From Debt Crisis, the End of Bailouts in Sight
headline.print_headline: End of Bailouts Near, Greece Prepares to Stagger Back From Debt Crisis

byline.original: By Milan Schreuer and Niki Kitsantonis

docs.abstract: Jennifer Lee and Pete Docter will take over as the chief creative officers at Disney Animation and Pixar following the resignation of John Lasseter.
docs.snippet: Jennifer Lee and Pete Docter will take over as the chief creative officers at Disney Animation and Pixar following the resignation of John Lasseter.
docs.lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — Pete Docter is a 6-foot-5 Minnesotan who comes across like Tom Hanks in “Big” and lives in a literal tree house. Jennifer Lee is a 5-foot-3 Rhode Islander and self-described former “flute-playing band nerd” who loves books and is known for her showstopping laugh.

headline.main: ‘Frozen’ and ‘Inside Out’ Directors to Succeed Lasseter at Disney and Pixar
headline.print_headline: Disney Picks New Chiefs Of Animation

docs.abstract: Jonathan Bush, a nephew and cousin of presidents and the founder of Athenahealth, which provides digital services to medical offices, resigned under pressure by the hedge fund Elliott Management.
docs.snippet: Jonathan Bush, a nephew and cousin of presidents and the founder of Athenahealth, which provides digital services to medical offices, resigned under pressure by the hedge fund Elliott Management.
docs.lead_paragraph: A member of one of America’s best-known political families resigned on Wednesday from the health care technology company he started more than two decades ago, in a victory for one of the world’s most powerful hedge funds.

headline.main: Bush Scion Is Out as Health Firm’s Chief After Intense Activist Campaign
headline.print_headline: Bush Scion Is Forced To Leave Health Firm

byline.original: By Kate Kelly and David Enrich

docs.abstract: Security companies are hoping to harness the potential of A.I., promising better service at lower prices. But experts say there are risks.
docs.snippet: Security companies are hoping to harness the potential of A.I., promising better service at lower prices. But experts say there are risks.
docs.lead_paragraph: Home security is expected to be a $47.5 billion business by 2020. Top-of-the-line systems can include alarms, cameras, dogs, guards and even secret passageways. But even the most sophisticated systems can have a fundamental flaw: human error.

headline.main: Can Artificial Intelligence Keep Your Home Secure?
headline.print_headline: Can Artificial Intelligence Keep Your Home Secure?

docs.abstract: Education debt is a priority for younger employees. A new program from the pharmaceutical company Abbott adds a twist: promoting retirement saving, too.
docs.snippet: Education debt is a priority for younger employees. A new program from the pharmaceutical company Abbott adds a twist: promoting retirement saving, too.
docs.lead_paragraph: As educational debt continues to mushroom, younger workers often have to choose between paying off their student loans and saving for retirement. Companies are starting to offer student loan payment benefits, in part to attract and keep workers in a strong economy.

headline.main: To Draw Workers, Employers Offer to Help With Student Loans
headline.print_headline: Employers Offer Student Loan Help to Entice Younger Workers

docs.abstract: A company’s app may offer more features than a visit to its site through the browser on your phone or tablet, but it may take up more space and resources on your device.
docs.snippet: A company’s app may offer more features than a visit to its site through the browser on your phone or tablet, but it may take up more space and resources on your device.
docs.lead_paragraph: Q. When researching a topic on a website, I frequently get a pop-up alert that suggests I use that same site’s mobile app for iOS. What is the downside of using the site’s app? Does the app track personal information?
